Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(mcp/rules): scope rule mutations by tenant

Labels are not globally unique. Project A and project B may both have a
rule with the same label. This patch makes add duplicate detection,
update, and remove honor the active project tenant instead of silently
falling back to the global tenant.

It fixes these cases:
- project-scoped duplicate detection searches only current project plus global
- project-scoped update sends the resolved tenant_id to the daemon
- project-scoped remove queues delete with the resolved tenant_id
- global update/remove still use the global tenant explicitly
